How to set java path in Ubuntu

export JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64

export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin

ubuntu@ubuntu-2204:/usr/bin$ vi ~/.bashrc

source ~/.bashrc

------------------
Install Maven on unbuntu

 sudo apt install maven

ubuntu@ubuntu-2204:~$ mvn -version
Apache Maven 3.6.3
Maven home: /usr/share/maven
Java version: 17.0.2, vendor: Private Build, runtime: /usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64
Default locale: en_US, platform encoding: UTF-8
OS name: "linux", version: "5.15.0-25-generic", arch: "amd64", family: "unix"
ubuntu@ubuntu-2204:~$
